    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-06-09T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-06-09T12:00:00-05:00" n="427"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d427">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">121.5622/12: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in Ecuador</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gonzalez</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-06-09T13:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 9, 1936—1 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>18. The Trade Agreements Committee has approved carrying forward studies on
                    Ecuador, and a skeleton committee has been set up for that purpose. This
                    information is to be regarded as strictly confidential until the Department
                    instructs you to open conversations on the subject with the Government of
                    Ecuador, which it does not contemplate doing for some time.</p>
                <p>In this connection the Department is instructing the Consulate General in
                    Guayaquil to forward certain statistical material. The purpose of this or any
                    other similar report should not be revealed and the Consulate General should
                    cooperate closely with Assistant Commercial Attaché Crilley to avoid
                    duplication. Mail paraphrase of this message to the Consul General in
                    Guayaquil.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
